Small mechanical task. Add a single roundtrip test to verify `capabilities.mcpServers` flows through the SkillsStore.

## Working directory

`/Users/vpulim/dev/ai/ax-next/.claude/worktrees/skills-mcp-bundling-phase-b`

## Context

- `@ax/skills` `SkillsStore` re-parses `manifest_yaml` on read into `SkillCapabilities` (see `packages/skills/src/store.ts`, specifically `rowToSummary` and `rowToDetail`).
- The previous commit on this branch added `mcpServers: McpServerSpec[]` to `SkillCapabilities` and made the manifest parser populate it.
- This task adds a test that asserts the roundtrip works end-to-end through real postgres (via testcontainers, like the existing tests). It does NOT change any production code.

## Step

Add this test inside the existing `describe('SkillsStore', ...)` block in `packages/skills/src/__tests__/store.test.ts` (insert it after the `getDefaults()` test cluster or any logical sibling location — pick a spot consistent with the file's structure):

```typescript
it('roundtrips capabilities.mcpServers through upsert + list + get', async () => {
  const db = makeKysely();
  await runSkillsMigration(db);
  const store = createSkillsStore(db);

  const yaml = `name: ghub
description: GitHub MCP bundle.
capabilities:
  mcpServers:
    - name: github
      transport: stdio
      command: npx
      args: ['-y', '@modelcontextprotocol/server-github']
`;
  await store.upsert({
    id: 'ghub',
    description: 'GitHub MCP bundle.',
    manifestYaml: yaml,
    bodyMd: '# ghub\n',
    version: 0,
  });

  const list = await store.list();
  const ghub = list.find((s) => s.id === 'ghub');
  expect(ghub?.capabilities.mcpServers).toHaveLength(1);
  expect(ghub?.capabilities.mcpServers[0]?.name).toBe('github');

  const detail = await store.get('ghub');
  expect(detail).not.toBeNull();
  expect(detail!.capabilities.mcpServers[0]?.transport).toBe('stdio');
  expect(detail!.capabilities.mcpServers[0]?.command).toBe('npx');
});
```

Confirm the upsert signature by reading the existing tests in the file (above the insertion site). The current shape uses `id` (not `skillId`) and version as a number. Do NOT change the existing tests or the store.

## Verify

```
pnpm test --filter @ax/skills 2>&1 | tail -20
```

Expected: previous 71 tests + 1 new = 72 passed.

```
pnpm build --filter @ax/skills 2>&1 | tail -5
```

Expected: clean.

## Commit

```
git add packages/skills/src
git commit -m "test(skills): roundtrip capabilities.mcpServers via store (Phase B step 2/3)"
```

## Report back

- Status: DONE / BLOCKED
- New commit SHA
- Test counts before/after
- Anything surprising

